\begin_layout Subsection
Target
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Complete,
 UI/UX friendly radio view:
 includes song and artist information,
 current progression in song,
 signal strength of FM radio,
 radio currently playing (with it's callsign).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Album cover view:
 full 128x128 JPEG of relevant album cover for currently playing song.
 Color mapped,
 and using the TJpgDec JPEG library to accomodate for the CC3200's smaller RAM (loading the image line-by-line).
 The trickiest part of our software suite.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Similar artists view:
 List of artists similar to the one currently playing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Artist biography view:
 Print out artist biography on OLED,
 make sure it is scrollable
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Genre tags:
 List relevant genres for the currently playing song.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Similar tracks:
 List similar tracks for the currently playing song.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Song lyrics:
 List song lyrics (if available through Musixmatch) for the currently playing song
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Remote functionality:
 volume up/down functionality,
 Mute functionality,
 playback last FM radio.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Stretch
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Interactive recommender system:
 Click on a recommended artist to view their artist bio,
 and top tracks.
 Click on a recommended track to see it's genre tags,
 and what it's recommended tracks are.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Complete FM History:
 Allow for a complete history of the FM radio's visited thus far,
 and allow the user to click and visit a previous one.
 For an 
\emph on
extra
\emph default
 stretch goal,
 allow the user to view what they heard on this FM radio.
 An even further stretch goal would be to persist this information across runtimes of the system.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Channel tuning:
 Use the channel/paging minus and plus buttons on the remote to flip between FM radio signals reliably.
 Would require a consistent step-size and bounds check algorithm.
\end_layout

